00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:16,000
 We understand. I mean, I understand the world is selling me.

197
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:20,000
 God's not mad at us and judging us because we pursue life in other areas.

198
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:26,000
 The things that we pursue that are false gods, that aren't enduring life,

199
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:30,000
 are the judgment.

200
00:16:30,000 --> 00:16:35,000
 We find ourselves having, like the rich young ruler, fleeting moments of satisfaction,

201
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:44,000
 vacation, and buzzes and highs, but the buzz always ends.

202
00:16:44,000 --> 00:16:49,000
 The intense pleasure isn't enough.

203
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:57,000
 The fleeting validation from another human being doesn't satisfy our soul.

204
00:16:57,000 --> 00:17:01,000
 And this is what it says in the scripture. It says in Proverbs chapter 19,

205
00:17:01,000 --> 00:17:09,000
 it says, "It's not good for men to be without knowledge."

206
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:13,000
 It says, "He who makes haste with his feet errs."

207
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:16,000
 And then it says, "When men suffers of the consequence of that,"

208
00:17:16,000 --> 00:17:19,000
 it says, "their heart rages against God."

209
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:22,000
 How many times have you in your life said, "God, what is up with you? Why can't I?"

210
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:26,000
 And he's just like, "Hey, listen, I want to bless you.

211
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:32,000
 Do this. Fill your earth with these things.

212
00:17:32,000 --> 00:17:36,000
 Walk with me and act like me. You're made in my image.

213
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:42,000
 And so what I filled your heart with and this Edenic setting that you're in with,

214
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:45,000
 fill your life with and you'll continue to experience the blessing."

215
00:17:45,000 --> 00:17:48,000
 God said, "Look here, I love you. Look at the world. I made it.

216
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:51,000
 It's beautiful and it's perfect. This is how you go through this world."

217
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:56,000
 Because you need to hear this. God understands right now that this world is not our home.

218
00:17:56,000 --> 00:17:59,000
 We are aliens and strangers in it.

219
00:17:59,000 --> 00:18:02,000
 We live our lives in a way that people go, "Who are you people

220
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:06,000
 that aren't trying to figure out how to find life on your own?"

221
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:11,000
 You live as if you have a script and an understanding and an insight

222
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,000
 that most men don't have.

223
00:18:13,000 --> 00:18:16,000
 Because even when evil befalls you, you don't freak out

224
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:20,000
 and get filled with bitterness and vengeance and rage.

225
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:25,000
 There is forgiveness. There is a perspective in your life

226
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,000
 that I want to know what the source of it is.

227
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:29,000
 And we go, "Well, here's the source of it.

228
00:18:29,000 --> 00:18:33,000
 My king has told me that the world that we're in is not the world he intended.

229
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,000
 The world that we're in is a world wracked with sin.

230
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:38,000
 Sometimes I know that part of the trouble I have is because I've made choices

231
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:41,000
 to not walk in the ancient paths where the good way is.

232
00:18:41,000 --> 00:18:44,000
 And so sometimes the trouble that I'm in is trouble that I brought on myself.

233
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:48,000
 But often I'm not doing anything except trying to live faithfully

234
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:51,000
 and there is loneliness because this world is broken.

235
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:55,000
 There is sickness and disease because this world is broken.

236
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,000
 There is betrayal because this world is broken.

237
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:00,000
 And Jesus tells me to take heart. This world isn't my home.

238
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:03,000
 Have courage. Speak hope into others that are in the world.

239
00:19:03,000 --> 00:19:07,000
 And one day it will be all that you long for.

240
00:19:07,000 --> 00:19:12,000
 Meanwhile, have peace.

241
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:18,000
 And yoke yourself with others who live according to the ancient path,

242
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:23,000
 who want to fill their relationships and fill their world with the good way.

243
00:19:23,000 --> 00:19:26,000
 I want to bless you. 1 John 5:3.

244
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:31,000
 This is the commandment of God, that we keep his commandments

245
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,000
 and his commandments are not burdensome.

246
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:36,000
 Listen, don't miss this. I'm going to show you some Scripture a little bit later

247
00:19:36,000 --> 00:19:39,000
 and a legalist will tell you, do these things and God will bless you.

248
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:45,000
 That's not your Bible. The Bible is, let me bless you, I love you. Do this.

249
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:49,000
 Do you understand that?

250
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:55,000
 The law that God gives us is basically instructions from a loving father

251
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,000
 and he's just saying, look, this is good for you.

252
00:19:57,000 --> 00:20:00,000
 Now listen, none of us do everything a loving father wants us to do.

253
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:02,000
 That's called sin.

254
00:20:02,000 --> 00:20:07,000
 And it leaves us broken hearted and it leaves us, when we choose to go this way,

255
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:11,000
 when God says that way, we've offended God, we're turning away from him.

256
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:14,000
 And that's where God says, listen, I understand why you do that

257
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:19,000
 because you come from a down line of rebels, but I'm going to make provision for you.

258
00:20:19,000 --> 00:20:23,000
 And when you turn the wrong way and you come to your senses, just acknowledge,

259
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,000
 this isn't the right way. Confess, which means to agree with.

260
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:28,000
 This isn't the right way. What am I doing? I've left the ancient paths.

261
00:20:28,000 --> 00:20:30,000
 I've turned to the left or to the right.

262
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:33,000
 I have not trusted in the Lord and leaned not on my own understanding.

263
00:20:33,000 --> 00:20:35,000
 I have not in all my ways acknowledged him.

264
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:37,000
 And that's why there is now pain.

265
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:39,000
 That's why there is now regret.

266
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:41,000
 That's why there is now shame.

267
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:42,000
 That's why there is now guilt.

268
00:20:42,000 --> 00:20:45,000
 Praise be to God who gave himself for me.

269
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,000
 Praise be to God for my living hope.

270
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:50,000
 Let me make amends with everybody that I've wronged in my going the wrong way.

271
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:54,000
 Let me celebrate my risen Lord and let me get back on the straight path.

272
00:20:54,000 --> 00:20:57,000
 Let me confess my sins to God that I might be forgiven.

273
00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:01,000
 And let me confess my sins to others that we might heal our relationship.

274
00:21:01,000 --> 00:21:05,000
 That's the word of God.

275
00:21:05,000 --> 00:21:09,000
 And off we go.

276
00:21:09,000 --> 00:21:14,000
 I love talking with you about how we live in light of eternity.

277
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:19,000
 In light of the reality of the horror of life without God.

278
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:21,000
 And in light of the hope that's coming with life with God.

279
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:24,000
 See, here's the thing. You just need to know this.

280
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:28,000
 If you're going home, if Jesus is the provision for your sin,

281
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:31,000
 if you've acknowledged that you have a tendency to leave the ancient past,

282
00:21:31,000 --> 00:21:33,000
 like all of us have and all of us do,

283
00:21:33,000 --> 00:21:35,000
 and you know that that's an offense to a holy God,

284
00:21:35,000 --> 00:21:39,000
 and you say, "God, I know the wages of my leaving you is death,

285
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:44,000
 "but I praise you that you've shown me that the free gift is eternal life,

286
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:48,000
 "is full and continual life with Jesus,

287
00:21:48,000 --> 00:21:50,000
 "but not just in a life to come,

288
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:55,000
 "but right now I can live a life that's different than the rich can live.

289
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:59,000
 "I can live a life that is extraordinary,

290
00:21:59,000 --> 00:22:02,000
 "almost alien-ish.

291
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:07,000
 "I'm not a slave to the world's demands.

292
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:11,000
 "I'm not going to be filled with its despair

293
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:14,000
 "because I'm going to live with a perspective

294
00:22:14,000 --> 00:22:18,000
 "that's just a little bit unusual

295
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:21,000
 "because I have more than the usual wisdom.

296
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:24,000
 "The Scripture says things which eye hasn't seen, ear hasn't heard,

297
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:26,000
 "things which don't enter into the hearts of common men.

298
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:32,000
 "All these things God has freely given to those who love him."

299
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:39,000
 And so we are people of great hope and great perception.

300
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:43,000
 And why we should discipline ourself, that's fine, you know, to have good bodies.

301
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:46,000
 It just says make sure you stay attentive

302
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:49,000
 to not just bodily discipline,

303
00:22:49,000 --> 00:22:51,000
 but especially to godliness for it's profitable.

304
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:53,000
 You're going to start to experience a little bit more now.

305
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,000
 Here's the thing.

306
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:57,000
 If you're going home, this is your hell.

307
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:00,000
 If you're going home to heaven, if Jesus is your king,

308
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:05,000
 this is as bad as it's ever going to get.

309
00:23:05,000 --> 00:23:10,000
 And if you're a person who rejects the provision and the kindness of God,

310
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:15,000
 you're living on an earth that is filled with what is called common grace.

311
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:20,000
 The rain falls on the wicked and the unjust,

312
00:23:20,000 --> 00:23:23,000
 just like it does on the righteous and the godly.

313
00:23:23,000 --> 00:23:25,000
 It waters your ground.

314
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:28,000
 When you're a sinner and you nick yourself and you start to bleed,

315
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:32,000
 God has in your body the ability for that blood to thicken,

316
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:35,000
 to coagulate, and to stop the bleeding.

317
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:40,000
 There is music on earth for the sinner and the righteous alike.

318
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,000
 There is the ability to experience temporary pleasure

319
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:47,000
 through human relationship for the sinner and the righteous alike.

320
00:23:47,000 --> 00:23:53,000
 If you are a rebel against God, this is your heaven.

321
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:58,000
 And it's never going to get better than this.

322
00:23:58,000 --> 00:24:00,000
 And so I don't want to say drink deeply,

323
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:03,000
 but what Solomon would say is, "Hey, yeah, eat, drink, and be merry,

324
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:08,000
 for tomorrow you die."

325
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:10,000
 To the believer, he would say, "Hey, listen, man, this world isn't your home.

326
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:12,000
 To live is Christ, to die is to gain.

327
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:15,000
 So eat, drink, and be merry, and all that you do, do it for the glory of God,

328
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:19,000
 for tomorrow you die and you're going home."

329
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:22,000
 One leaving hell behind forever,

330
00:24:22,000 --> 00:24:28,000
 the other losing even a whisper of what heaven might be like.

331
00:24:28,000 --> 00:24:32,000
 So what do we do in light of this?

332
00:24:32,000 --> 00:24:36,000
 The answer is, is we start to enjoy what God wants us to enjoy right now,

333
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:39,000
 because what God has done is he's made provision for us right now

334
00:24:39,000 --> 00:24:43,000
 on how to experience more than usual,

335
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:49,000
 extraordinary, supernatural life now.

336
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:53,000
 That's who we are if you're a believer.

337
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:58,000
 There is a condition upon you when you walk in the ancient past

338
00:24:58,000 --> 00:25:02,000
 where the good way is when you walk in it,

339
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:05,000
 because God blesses you and you no longer think the commandments of God

340
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:07,000
 are burdensome or rules that you've got to perform

341
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:10,000
 or things you have to do so he doesn't backhand you,

342
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:16,000
 but you realize it's the words of a loving father

343
00:25:16,000 --> 00:25:19,000
 and just trying to encourage you and help you.

344
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:21,000
 And he knows you're not going to be perfect, child,

345
00:25:21,000 --> 00:25:24,000
 so I make provision for you.

346
00:25:24,000 --> 00:25:28,000
 The righteous falls seven times and gets back up again,

347
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:30,000
 with God there to encourage you and to bring you back to completion,

348
00:25:30,000 --> 00:25:32,000
 what he's begun.

349
00:25:32,000 --> 00:25:34,000
 And the more you see the goodness of his way,

350
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,000
 the more you walk according to it,

351
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:39,000
 the more you escape the horror of self-pain.

352
00:25:39,000 --> 00:25:41,000
 You still live in a world that's broken,

353
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:45,000
 but even then you can sing because you understand why.

354
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:47,000
 Watch this, Ecclesiastes 7.

355
00:25:47,000 --> 00:25:50,000
 It just says this, "A good name is better than good ointment,"

356
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:55,000
 is what my Bible says your Bible might say is better than perfume.

357
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:57,000
 Okay? Which is kind of funny.

358
00:25:57,000 --> 00:26:00,000
 I mean, if I could have perfume or a good name, I mean, give me the good name.

359
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:04,000
 But the idea here of what perfume represents or oil or good ointment,

360
00:26:04,000 --> 00:26:10,000
 it represents the sense of joy, it represents prosperity.

361
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:12,000
 But here's the thing, a good name is enduring.

362
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:16,000
 When you put perfume on, it's not long before just the joy

363
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:19,000
 and the fleetingness of the moment leaves you,

364
00:26:19,000 --> 00:26:22,000
 and you're left with a rank life.

365
00:26:22,000 --> 00:26:25,000
 No matter how sweet you can make yourself smell for a moment,

366
00:26:25,000 --> 00:26:29,000
 you're not really experiencing the richness and the sweetness of life

367
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:30,000
 that God intends for you.

368
00:26:30,000 --> 00:26:34,000
 And so what he's just saying is don't look for temporary things to please you.

369
00:26:34,000 --> 00:26:36,000
 And that's why he says in this next little line,

370
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:38,000
 "The day of one's death is better than the day of one's birth."

371
00:26:38,000 --> 00:26:40,000
 You have to follow Hebrew poetry here.

372
00:26:40,000 --> 00:26:43,000
 What he's saying in verse 1a, if you want to call it that,

373
00:26:43,000 --> 00:26:48,000
 in Ecclesiastes 7, he's just saying, "Listen, if you live a good life,

374
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:50,000
 and when you die, that's better than the day of one's birth."

375
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:53,000
 Why? Because the day of one's birth is joyful,

376
00:26:53,000 --> 00:26:56,000
 and there's nothing but the potential for prosperity ahead,

377
00:26:56,000 --> 00:26:58,000
 but there's also drama,

378
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:03,000
 and there's also the potential to give yourself the fleeting things.

379
00:27:03,000 --> 00:27:08,000
 And what Solomon is going to say is you might have moments with just real sweetness,

380
00:27:08,000 --> 00:27:10,000
 but in the end, you're going to have a rank life

381
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:13,000
 if you don't be attentive to the ways of God.

382
00:27:13,000 --> 00:27:16,000
 And so Solomon is saying, "Man, it's better that you've lived a long life

383
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:20,000
 and been faithful than just starting where you may screw up."

384
00:27:20,000 --> 00:27:21,000
 That's kind of his perspective,

385
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:23,000
 because what he's going to do the rest of chapter 7

386
00:27:23,000 --> 00:27:26,000
 is he's going to kind of walk through, and he's going to tell you,

387
00:27:26,000 --> 00:27:29,000
 "Hey, there's some people that when they prosper, it screws them up,

388
00:27:29,000 --> 00:27:32,000
 and there's some people when they go through suffering, it screws them up

389
00:27:32,000 --> 00:27:35,000
 because they don't understand how to handle prosperity,

390
00:27:35,000 --> 00:27:39,000
 or they don't have any category to explain corruption."

391
00:27:39,000 --> 00:27:42,000
 So what Solomon's going to do to help you is in verse 2, he says this.

392
00:27:42,000 --> 00:27:46,000
 He says, "Listen, it's better to go to a house of mourning

393
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:50,000
 than it is to go to a house of feasting."

394
00:27:50,000 --> 00:27:52,000
 You ought to hang out at funerals more than parties,

395
00:27:52,000 --> 00:27:56,000
 because when you're at a funeral, you see what ultimately matters.

396
00:27:56,000 --> 00:27:58,000
 As we were singing here, I don't know if your phones dinged,

397
00:27:58,000 --> 00:28:03,000
 if you follow different news channels, but Barbara Bush died.

398
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:05,000
 Former first lady, the president of the United States.

399
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:09,000
 It was interesting because I'd seen, we knew that Barbara Bush was sick,

400
00:28:09,000 --> 00:28:11,000
 and all people are going to end up where Barbara Bush does

401
00:28:11,000 --> 00:28:14,000
 in terms of passing through this earth where our earthly bodies

402
00:28:14,000 --> 00:28:18,000
 that are condemned to death until God resurrects our bodies,

403
00:28:18,000 --> 00:28:20,000
 some to judgment and some to life.

404
00:28:20,000 --> 00:28:24,000
 Barbara Bush, there was a famous commencement speech she gave

405
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:27,000
 at an all-girls school, and one of the things she said at the end of the day,

406
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:31,000
 "You're not going to, at the end of your life, want to have won one more case,

407
00:28:31,000 --> 00:28:36,000
 gotten one more nice outfit, won one more argument.

408
00:28:36,000 --> 00:28:42,000
 You won't regret one test that you didn't do as well in as you wish you would have.

409
00:28:42,000 --> 00:28:47,000
 What you're going to regret are the times you didn't love and care for people,

410
00:28:47,000 --> 00:28:53,000
 the times you didn't prepare yourself to invest in the only things that matter,

411
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:58,000
 and everything you gave away to fleeting things are not going to be sweet to you

412
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:00,000
 on the deathbed."

413
00:29:00,000 --> 00:29:08,000
 One time, there was a guy that walked in, and I have sat in chairs

414
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:14,000
 next to beds of billionaires feeding them ice chips,

415
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:21,000
 where I have seen their wealth be useless to them.

416
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:25,000
 I've been in the homes of people who were in palliative care,

417
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:29,000
 and their homes, these homes that I will never live in,

418
00:29:29,000 --> 00:29:32,000
 of people who are doing exceedingly well,

419
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:37,000
 and the one man whose home I was in was surrounded by immense wealth this one time,

420
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:40,000
 and in a sense, he didn't say this, but another time in a story like this,

421
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:43,000
 you might say, "What is all this that is around you?"

422
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:48,000
 And the answer is, "These are the things that make a deathbed terrible."

423
00:29:48,000 --> 00:29:53,000
 Because you feel like you're letting go of everything you've ever invested in.

424
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:57,000
 Instead of following the counsel of God, who wants you to go,

425
00:29:57,000 --> 00:30:05,000
 "Hey, while you're alive, use the things that I've given you to bless others."

426
00:30:05,000 --> 00:30:09,000
 Not to just continue to mount up comfort for yourself.

427
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:12,000
 You're not here to make a living. You're here to make a difference.

428
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:17,000
 "It is more blessed," Jesus says, the Bible says, "to give than receive."

429
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:20,000
 He doesn't tell you, "If you don't give more than you receive, you're going to hell."

430
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:26,000
 He says, "You want to experience a little bit of heaven on earth?

431
00:30:26,000 --> 00:30:30,000
 Then be like me."

432
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:35,000
 "For though I was rich, I became poor, that through my poverty you might become rich."

433
00:30:35,000 --> 00:30:38,000
 Who do we get in this room and sing songs about?

434
00:30:38,000 --> 00:30:41,000
 Who's seated at the right hand of God? Who's been given a name above all names?

435
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:47,000
 The answer is Jesus.

436
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:50,000
 I think about William Borden.

437
00:30:50,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 You may never have heard of William Borden before.

438
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:55,000
 His name is Borden of Yale.

439
00:30:55,000 --> 00:31:03,000
 You know Borden, this is a picture of him, because you drink his family's wealth.

440
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:05,000
 Elsie the cow comes from the Borden family.

441
00:31:05,000 --> 00:31:09,000
 This is the Borden dairy dynasty.

442
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:13,000
 At the turn of the 19th century, moving into the 20th century,

443
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:17,000
 young William Borden graduated from high school.

444
00:31:17,000 --> 00:31:24,000
 As part of his graduation gift, his wealthy family gave him a chance to travel around the world.

445
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 Bill Borden was a man that went around the world.

446
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:30,000
 When he went around the world, though, he went with a man of faith.

447
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:33,000
 That man of faith didn't just take him skiing in the Swiss Alps.

448
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:37,000
 He took him to certain places where there were people groups that did not know about the ancient past.

449
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:41,000
 There were people that had been part of human history that had rejected God and his ways

450
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:44,000
 and had given themselves over to superstition and myth.

451
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:50,000
 Entire generations and cultures were living in the midst of paganism.

452
00:31:50,000 --> 00:31:54,000
 Bill Borden saw this.

453
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:56,000
 He was a man who had a faith.

454
00:31:56,000 --> 00:32:01,000
 While he was over there, God sparked in his life a desire for the nations to understand what he understood.

455
00:32:01,000 --> 00:32:08,000
 Not to have the wealth that he did, but to have the wealth of understanding that the grace of God had given him.

456
00:32:08,000 --> 00:32:12,000
 So Bill Borden went back home.

457
00:32:12,000 --> 00:32:16,000
 He went and got his education at the time at Yale University.

458
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:19,000
 While he was there, his freshman year, when he showed up,

459
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:25,000
 the president of the university spoke up and gave a speech to all the incoming students.

460
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:31,000
 He told them, "You all must have a fixed purpose in life."

461
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:34,000
 Borden walked out of that room incredibly agitated.

462
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:36,000
 His friends that he was just making said, "Why are you so frustrated?"

463
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:40,000
 He wrote down, "This president neglected to say what our purpose should be."

464
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:43,000
 Can I have my stick back?

465
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:47,000
 He just said, "You've got to have a great purpose. You've gone on a journey in this life.

466
00:32:47,000 --> 00:32:53,000
 You're not at the end. You're at the beginning. This is the beginning."

467
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:55,000
 He said, "You must have a purpose."

468
00:32:55,000 --> 00:33:02,000
 But he says, "He neglected to tell us where we should find our purpose

469
00:33:02,000 --> 00:33:06,000
 and where we should get an ability to persevere in our purpose,

470
00:33:06,000 --> 00:33:09,000
 where we get the strength to resist the temptations

471
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:13,000
 that will have us only seeking after fleeting joys while we're here.

472
00:33:13,000 --> 00:33:17,000
 This man failed us."

473
00:33:17,000 --> 00:33:21,000
 And so what he started to do is he said, "I'm going to show you guys where purpose comes from."

474
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:25,000
 He said, "Wait until you go on the mission field to go reach these unreached people."

475
00:33:25,000 --> 00:33:28,000
 He went to his fellow students at Yale, and he turned to one friend and he said,

476
00:33:28,000 --> 00:33:32,000
 "I'd love you to get up with me in the morning and pray that God will allow us to resist temptation,

477
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:35,000
 that God will allow us to live according to the purposes that he's given us as men on earth

478
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:38,000
 that are moving through. This world is not our home."

479
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:41,000
 And every morning, he said, Bill and this one guy would get up, he would read his Bible,

480
00:33:41,000 --> 00:33:44,000
 and he would tell his friend what the Bible meant

481
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:47,000
 and how God had given them a purpose there that was greater than making fortunes

482
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:50,000
 or living underneath the fortunes that others have made.

483
00:33:50,000 --> 00:33:53,000
 And then two people joined, and then three people joined, and then four people joined.

484
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:56,000
 One guy just said this, "When we met Bill,

485
00:33:56,000 --> 00:34:00,000
 it became obvious to us that there was something about him

486
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:03,000
 that strengthened the rest of us."

487
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:06,000
 And what it was, it was a man with a conviction. It was a man that understood things

488
00:34:06,000 --> 00:34:09,000
 which Yale students didn't understand, Yale presidents didn't understand.

489
00:34:09,000 --> 00:34:13,000
 The philosophies and elementary instructions of the world weren't giving them that purpose.

490
00:34:13,000 --> 00:34:18,000
 And Bill looked around, he saw the immorality and the hopelessness and the despair of men that were living.

491
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:22,000
 By the time he graduated four years later, it wasn't one or two men that were with him.

492
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:26,000
 1,000 of the 1,300 Yale students were in Bible studies

493
00:34:26,000 --> 00:34:29,000
 that Bill had coordinated and led at Yale University.

494
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:31,000
 Did you hear that?

495
00:34:31,000 --> 00:34:35,000
 1,300 students at Yale University at the time, and Bill gave them a purpose.

496
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:38,000
 And there was a revival that broke out on the Yale campus.

497
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:42,000
 After he broke out from the Yale campus, he went on to Princeton

498
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:45,000
 to get further theological training.

499
00:34:45,000 --> 00:34:49,000
 And while he was there, he became convinced that God wanted him to reach

500
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:53,000
 about 10 million Muslims that lived in China.

501
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:57,000
 And so he told his family that he was going to go and give his life

502
00:34:57,000 --> 00:35:00,000
 to reaching these people who did not know Christ and were in bondage to Islam,

503
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:03,000
 living inside of China.

504
00:35:03,000 --> 00:35:07,000
 His dad said, "If you leave, you'll never have any part in the family business."

505
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:11,000
 And so he took his Bible and he wrote up front, he said, "No reserves.

506
00:35:11,000 --> 00:35:14,000
 My father has told me there will be no fortune if I don't go back and live in the family

507
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:16,000
 because my dad was okay with me having a faith.

508
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:19,000
 He just didn't want my faith to inform everything that I did.

509
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:21,000
 Don't be too radical.

510
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:26,000
 Don't be too serious about heaven and hell and the ancient past."

511
00:35:26,000 --> 00:35:29,000
 "No reserves," he wrote in his Bible.

512
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:34,000
 And then he got over there, and as he got on the ship,

513
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:38,000
 he actually was going to sail first to Cairo because it was in Cairo

514
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:43,000
 that he was going to learn Arabic so he could speak to the Muslims inside China.

515
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:46,000
 And as he got on that boat, he wrote down, "No retreats."

516
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:49,000
 There's no turning back.

517
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:56,000
 He arrived there in basically January of 1919,

518
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:59,000
 and he was there learning Arabic, and three months later,

519
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:06,000
 he contracted spinal meningitis, and 19 days after that, he died.

520
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:13,000
 And right before he died, he wrote in his Bible, "No regrets."

521
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:18,000
 You see, the Bible says that God should--we pray in Psalm 90, verse 12,

522
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:21,000
 that we should pray that God will teach us to number our days

523
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:23,000
 that we might present to him a life of wisdom.

524
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:28,000
 One of the things that is just certainly true of most Yalies, most Porches,

525
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:30,000
 is that we go, "Well, I'm not really sure when I'm going to die,

526
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:33,000
 but it certainly isn't soon.

527
00:36:33,000 --> 00:36:37,000
 So I'll just do my thing for a while, and I'll be successful,

528
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:39,000
 and then I'll move to significance."

529
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:44,000
 And Borden of Yale said, "No, I am going to live right now

530
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:46,000
 in light of what I believe is the most important thing to do."

531
00:36:46,000 --> 00:36:48,000
 And he gave his life to it.

532
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:52,000
 Not just because he went over to Cairo and eventually was making his way to China,

533
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:57,000
 but while he was at Yale, he distinguished himself and set a generation on fire.

534
00:36:57,000 --> 00:37:02,000
 There was a trust that had been given to him that he heard about before he died,

535
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:06,000
 and he intended that that entire trust would be given to people

536
00:37:06,000 --> 00:37:10,000
 that would study the Scripture and teach it in all of its fullness

537
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:13,000
 with all of the solid doctrine that he had learned himself

538
00:37:13,000 --> 00:37:16,000
 as a young theological student in his later training.

539
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:24,000
 And the legacy of Borden of Yale's life has led to multiple lives

540
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:28,000
 being transformed for Christ.

541
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:31,000
 See, he didn't know that he was going to die in his early 20s,

542
00:37:31,000 --> 00:37:36,000
 but he was ready, and he did what he should do on that journey

543
00:37:36,000 --> 00:37:37,000
 to make the most of it.

544
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:43,000
 No reserves, no retreats, no regrets.

