 He just says this in Ecclesiastes 12, verses 1-8, he just says this,

565
00:38:56,000 --> 00:38:59,000
 "Remember also your Creator in the days of your youth."

566
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:04,000
 This is Solomon at the end of his life, when he had spent his youth

567
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:07,000
 and his strength and his riches in fleeting things,

568
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:10,000
 and he had lost his good name.

569
00:39:10,000 --> 00:39:15,000
 He's saying, "Oh, don't make the mistake that I did."

570
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:18,000
 "Remember your Creator while you're young, before the evil days come

571
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:21,000
 and the years draw near, when you will say, 'I have no delight in them,'

572
00:39:21,000 --> 00:39:24,000
 because as you get old, you can't do the things you used to do,

573
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:25,000
 and the world changes."

574
00:39:25,000 --> 00:39:27,000
 And so he uses metaphorical language.

575
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:30,000
 Watch this, "Before the sun and the light and the moon and the stars are darkened

576
00:39:30,000 --> 00:39:33,000
 and clouds return after the rain, there is such a thing called

577
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:35,000
 seasonal affective disorder."

578
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:36,000
 Have you ever heard of that?

579
00:39:36,000 --> 00:39:40,000
 I mean, literally, the acronym for it is SAD.

580
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:45,000
 And it's called SAD, and a lot of folks up in Washington State have it,

581
00:39:45,000 --> 00:39:48,000
 because it's just gloomy and it rains, it's dark and it's cloudy,

582
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:51,000
 there's never any sun, there's never any break in the weather,

583
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:54,000
 and literally in fall through winter, they see people,

584
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:58,000
 there's a spike in depression, a spike in suicide, a spike in despair,

585
00:39:58,000 --> 00:40:03,000
 and they call it SAD, seasonal affective disorder.

586
00:40:03,000 --> 00:40:06,000
 And really what Solomon is doing, long before we had people who put labels

587
00:40:06,000 --> 00:40:09,000
 on such things, he's saying, "That's what the end of life is like.

588
00:40:09,000 --> 00:40:12,000
 There's nothing but clouds and then rain, and the clouds come back again

